abla^2 f = {{\partial^2 f}\over{\partial x_1^2}} + \dots + {{\partial^2f}\over{\partial x_n^2}} = {{n-1}\over{r}}g'(r) + g''(r)$$for $	extbf{x} 
eq 0$. Deduce from the previous part that, if $
abla^2 f = 0$, then$$f(	extbf{x}) = {a\over{|	extbf{x}|^{n-2}}} + b,	ext{ }	extbf{x} 
eq 0,$$where $a$ and $b$ are constants. I am stuck on this problem. Can anyone give me a hint?
